import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Installation">
  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    Rep-li-bot requires Windows 10 or later (64-bit). Follow these steps to install.
  </p>

  <h3>Download</h3>
  <p>
    Download the latest installer from the <a href="/download">download page</a>
    or from <a href="https://github.com/andyjm2k/Rep-li-bot/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Releases</a>.
  </p>

  <h3>Run the Installer</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Double-click <code>Replibot Setup X.X.X.exe</code></li>
    <li>If prompted by User Account Control, click "Yes"</li>
    <li>Follow the setup wizard instructions</li>
    <li>Choose your installation location (default is recommended)</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>AI Provider Setup</h3>
  <p>
    During installation, you'll be prompted to configure your AI provider.
    You can skip this and configure it later from within the app.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Provider Label</strong> - A friendly name (e.g., "ChatGPT")</li>
    <li><strong>Base URL</strong> - The API endpoint (e.g., <code>https://api.openai.com/v1</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Model</strong> - The model name (e.g., <code>gpt-4</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>API Key</strong> - Your API key for authentication</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>First Launch</h3>
  <p>After installation, launch Rep-li-bot from:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Start Menu → "Rep-li-bot"</li>
    <li>Desktop shortcut (if created)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Troubleshooting</h3>

  <h4>Installation fails</h4>
  <p>
    Make sure you have administrator privileges and that Windows Defender
    or other security software isn't blocking the installer.
  </p>

  <h4>App won't launch</h4>
  <p>
    Verify your Windows version is 10 or later and that you have a display adapter
    with WebGL support.
  </p>

  <h4>AI features don't work</h4>
  <p>
    Check your AI configuration in Settings → AI Settings panel.
    Ensure your API key is valid and you have an active subscription.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
